14:29:58.327 [INFO] # Design constraints for a household assistant

14:29:58.327 [INFO] Before I let this idea become a "platform," I want to write down the constraints that make it worth building at all.

14:29:58.327 [INFO] If I do not do this early, the project will drift toward the usual failure modes: too much scope, too much enchantment, too much surveillance posture, too much hidden complexity, and not enough usefulness on an ordinary Wednesday.

14:29:58.327 [INFO] ## 1. It has to reduce load, not create a new hobby

14:29:58.327 [INFO] The assistant is not allowed to become another dependent system that needs constant tuning, prompting, babysitting, dashboard grooming, or ritual maintenance just to justify its existence.

14:29:58.327 [INFO] If it saves time only after I spend three weekends integrating and curating everything, then it is a workshop project, not household infrastructure.

14:29:58.327 [INFO] The test is simple:

14:29:58.328 [INFO] - does it make this week lighter

